MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: By_him_the_curze_d_kings_of_gloreday_seem_a_way_less_dim
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 97
  mythName: By him the curze'd kings of gloreday seem a way less dim
  omens:
  - '1. Snow begins to fall. First a flurry, then a

    veil that covers the whole
    Realm. Vision is

    limited to shouting distance. This

    remains until the
    Ogre dies or stops it.'
  - '2. Two elderly weavers stagger through the

    snow. They were captives in
    the Ogre''s

    castle. He released them because they

    would not work fast
    enough.'
  - '3. The Ogre watches the Company from the

    veil of snow. He''s looking for
    a Knight to

    capture, to guard his castle. Although he

    cannot die, he
    won''t fight on long if hurt.'
  - '4. Shivering in the snow, a stinging

    crocodile. It will lead Knights to
    the castle

    and a tunnel into the catacombs below.'
  - '5. An ancient graveyard on a hilltop, names

    forgotten. Some know that the
    Ogre''s soul

    is hidden in the first skull buried here.'
  - '6. Having gathered enough servants to live

    a comfortable life, the Ogre
    bellows out in

    coarse laughter, heard across the Realm.

    His reluctant
    Knights gather taxes

    weekly, taking more than any can afford.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. Snow begins to fall. First a flurry, then a

    veil that
    covers the whole Realm. Vision is

    limited to shouting distance. This

    remains
    until the Ogre dies or stops it.

    2. Two elderly weavers stagger through
    the

    snow. They were captives in the Ogre''s

    castle. He released them
    because they

    would not work fast enough.

    3. The Ogre watches the Company
    from the

    veil of snow. He''s looking for a Knight to

    capture, to guard
    his castle. Although he

    cannot die, he won''t fight on long if hurt.

    4.
    Shivering in the snow, a stinging

    crocodile. It will lead Knights to the
    castle

    and a tunnel into the catacombs below.

    5. An ancient graveyard
    on a hilltop, names

    forgotten. Some know that the Ogre''s soul

    is hidden
    in the first skull buried here.

    6. Having gathered enough servants to live

    a
    comfortable life, the Ogre bellows out in

    coarse laughter, heard across
    the Realm.

    His reluctant Knights gather taxes

    weekly, taking more than
    any can afford.

    Cast

    The Ogre, the Repulsive Pretender

    VIG 18,
    CLA 10, SPI 2, 8 GD

    A2 (gnarled muscles), bony knife (d8),

    crooked
    horn (d10), foul finery (see below)

    Recovers from any harm while his soul
    is

    safely hidden. Hates being looked at.

    Wants to live a lazy life
    of luxury.

    Stinging Crocodile, Nattlesnap

    VIG 10, CLA 5, SPI 5, 3 GD

    Jaws
    (d8, wound causes a painful sting, lose

    d6 SPI). Hates the Ogre, who banished
    him.

    Reluctant Knights of the Ogre

    VIG 13, CLA 10, SPI 10, 5 GD

    A2
    (battered helm and shield)

    Mace (d8 hefty), shield (d4)

    Only serve
    while the Ogre holds their kin.

    From sluggal umbrage knit a gastrell, deck''d
    in grile, and grim'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Ogre, the Repulsive Pretender
    statBlock: 'VIG 18, CLA 10, SPI 2, 8 GD

      A2 (gnarled muscles), bony knife
      (d8),'
    notes: 'crooked horn (d10), foul finery (see below)

      Recovers from any
      harm while his soul is

      safely hidden. Hates being looked at.

      Wants
      to live a lazy life of luxury.'
  - name: Stinging Crocodile, Nattlesnap
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 5, SPI 5, 3 GD

      Jaws (d8, wound causes a painful
      sting, lose'
    notes: d6 SPI). Hates the Ogre, who banished him.
  - name: Reluctant Knights of the Ogre
    statBlock: 'VIG 13, CLA 10, SPI 10, 5 GD

      A2 (battered helm and shield)'
    notes: 'Mace (d8 hefty), shield (d4)

      Only serve while the Ogre holds their
      kin.

      From sluggal umbrage knit a gastrell, deck''d in grile, and grim

      By
      him the curze''d kings of gloreday seem a way less dim

      FOUL FINERY

      A
      cloak of... And a crown of...

      1 Skin Bones

      2 Feathers Twigs

      3
      Moss Dead birds

      4 Stomachs Eyes

      5 Bark Teeth

      6 Matted
      hair Rocks

      Ogre

      Dwelling: Silk-farming monks ~ Sanctum: Canyon
      vista ~ Monument: Floral chapel

      Hazard: Tangling moss ~ Curse: Taunting
      mirage ~ Ruin: Vine-choked tower

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: FOUL FINERY
    rows:
    - 1 Skin Bones
    - 2 Feathers Twigs
    - 3 Moss Dead birds
    - 4 Stomachs Eyes
    - 5 Bark Teeth
    - '6 Matted hair Rocks

      Ogre'
  dwelling: Silk-farming monks
  sanctum: Canyon vista
  monument: Floral chapel
  hazard: Tangling moss
  curse: Taunting mirage
  ruin: Vine-choked tower
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
